A proclamacion, set furth by the kynges Maiestye with thassent of his derest vncle, Edward Duke of Somerset, gouernour of his moste royall persone, and of his realmes, dominions and subiectes protector, and others of his most honorable counsayle for the executyng of a lawe martiall for payne of death against rebellors and their vpstyrrors Proclamations. 1549-07-16 England and Wales. Sovereign (1547-1553 : Edward VI)
1 sheet ([1] p.)
In ædibus Richardi Graftoni Regij impressoris Cum priuilegio ad imprimendum solum, Excusum Londini : [1549]
Publication date from STC. STC 7827= 2 leaves; British Library and Chatsworth, Bakewell, Derbyshire (Duke of Devonshire) are only known copies; not filmed. Reproduction of the original in the Society of Antiquaries.
